9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 570, L.D. 1376, “An Act to Increase the
10 Acceptable Level of Alcohol in a Low-alcohol Spirits Product and to Increase Availability
11 of Those Products”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Increase the Availability of Ready-to-drink Beverages Containing Spirits'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 28-A MRSA §2, sub-§31, as amended by PL 2019, c. 404, §2, is further
17 amended to read:
18 31. Spirits. "Spirits" means any liquor produced by distillation or, if produced by any
19 other process, strengthened or fortified by the addition of spirits of any kind. "Spirits" does
20 not include low-alcohol spirits products, a spirits cocktail product or fortified wine.
21 Beginning July 1, 2019, "spirits" "Spirits" does not mean an additive or flavoring, such as
22 an extract or concentrate, that:
23 A. Contains alcohol;
24 B. Is not intended to be consumed alone as a beverage or a food product but serves as
25 a flavor enhancement to a beverage or a food product; and
26 C. Is not subject to excise tax under chapter 65.
27 Sec. 2. 28-A MRSA §2, sub-§31-E is enacted to read:
28 31-E. Spirits cocktail product. "Spirits cocktail product" means a product packaged
29 as a single-serving ready-to-drink beverage containing spirits that contains more than 8%
30 alcohol by volume but no more than 15% alcohol by volume.
31 Sec. 3. 28-A MRSA §13, as repealed and replaced by PL 2021, c. 658, §49, is
32 amended to read:
33 §13. Low-alcohol spirits products and spirits cocktail products sold by wine licensees
