3 Sec. 7. 28-A MRSA §1355-A, sub-§5, ¶H, as amended by PL 2021, c. 658, §226,
4 is further amended to read:
5 H. Notwithstanding paragraph D, a holder of a small distillery license that sells its
6 products spirits or offers complimentary samples of its products spirits directly to
7 consumers for on-premises consumption under paragraph F‑1 or under subsection 2,
8 paragraph B or I may pay the bureau the difference between the distillery's price
9 charged to the bureau and the discounted retail price charged by the bureau under
10 section 606, subsection 4‑B. A small distillery is not required to transport spirits that
11 will be sold for on-premises consumption as described in this paragraph to a warehouse
12 operated by the bureau or by the wholesale spirits provider. A holder of a small
