18 Sec. 8. 28-A MRSA §1355-A, sub-§5, ¶J, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 658, §226,
19 is amended to read:
20 J. A holder of a distillery or small distillery license may produce low-alcohol spirits
21 products and spirits cocktail products.
22 (1) If a small distillery license holder produces low-alcohol spirits products or
23 spirits cocktail products pursuant to this paragraph, the combined total of spirits,
24 spirits cocktail products and low-alcohol spirits products produced at the small
25 distillery may not exceed 50,000 gallons per year.
26 (2) The holder of a distillery license or a small distillery license that produces
27 spirits cocktail products shall deliver spirits cocktail products to licensed retailers
28 through a wholesale licensee in the same manner as a winery that produces and
29 bottles more than 50,000 gallons of wine per year delivers wine to licensed retailers
30 as provided in section 1361, subsection 4. This subparagraph does not apply to
31 spirits cocktail products sold at the distillery licensee's manufacturing facility or at
32 an off-premises location for which the distillery has a small distillery license
33 pursuant to paragraph B.
34 Sec. 9. 28-A MRSA §1652, sub-§1-A, as amended by PL 2021, c. 8, §8, is further
35 amended to read:
36 1-A. Excise tax on low-alcohol spirits products, spirits cocktail products and
37 fortified wines. An excise tax is imposed on the privilege of manufacturing and selling
38 low-alcohol spirits products, spirits cocktail products and fortified wines in the State.
39 Except as provided in subsection 2‑A, the in-state manufacturer or importing wholesale
40 licensee shall pay an excise tax of $1.24 per gallon on all low-alcohol spirits products,
41 spirits cocktail products and fortified wines manufactured in or imported into the State.
42 Sec. 10. 28-A MRSA §1652, sub-§2-A, as amended by PL 2021, c. 8, §10, is
43 further amended to read:
