1 2-A. Excise tax due; exemption. On the 15th day of each month, every distillery,
2 brewery and winery shall pay the excise taxes due on malt liquor, wine, sprits cocktail
3 products and low-alcohol spirits products that that brewery or winery removed from areas
4 required to be bonded by the Federal Government. Malt liquor, wine, spirits cocktail
5 products or low-alcohol spirits products that a brewery or winery removes from areas
6 required to be bonded by the Federal Government for sale to an out-of-state wholesaler for
7 resale in another state or for sale under section 1357 directly to a consumer located in
8 another state are exempt from excise tax under this section.
9 Sec. 11. 28-A MRSA §1652, sub-§4, as amended by PL 2021, c. 658, §264, is
10 further amended to read:
11 4. Excise tax accounts and adjustments. The bureau shall open an excise tax account
12 with each wholesale licensee and each certificate of approval holder and make the
13 following adjustments when appropriate. As used in this subsection, "certificate of
14 approval holder" means an in-state manufacturer of malt liquor, wine, spirits cocktail
15 products or low-alcohol spirits products licensed under section 1355‑A or an out-of-state
16 manufacturer of or out-of-state wholesaler of malt liquor, wine, spirits cocktail products or
17 low-alcohol spirits products that has been issued a certificate of approval under section
18 1361.
19 A. The bureau may grant credits and make tax adjustments that it determines the
20 wholesale licensee or certificate of approval holder is entitled to upon the filing of
21 affidavits in the form prescribed by the bureau.
22 B. The bureau shall refund all excise tax paid by the wholesale licensee or certificate
23 of approval holder on all malt liquor, wine, spirits cocktail products or low-alcohol
24 spirits products that have been destroyed as long as the quantity and size are verified
25 by the bureau and the destruction is witnessed by an authorized representative of the
26 bureau.
27 C. If a wholesale licensee's inventories are destroyed by fire, flood or other natural
28 disaster, the bureau may refund the excise tax on the wholesale licensee's inventories.
29 D. Any wholesale licensee selling malt liquor, wine, spirits cocktail products or low-
30 alcohol spirits products to an instrumentality, a licensee for resale to an airline, a
31 training site or a ship chandler shall present proof of that sale to the bureau. The bureau
32 shall grant to the wholesale licensee a credit of all state excise tax paid in connection
33 with that sale under the following conditions.
34 (1) The bureau shall grant a credit for the excise tax on malt liquor, wine, spirits
35 cocktail products or low-alcohol spirits products sold by wholesale licensees to any
36 instrumentality of the United States or any Maine National Guard state training site
37 exempted by the bureau.
38 (2) The bureau shall grant a credit for the excise tax on malt liquor, wine, spirits
39 cocktail products or low-alcohol spirits products sold to any ship chandler as long
40 as the malt liquor, wine, spirits cocktail products and low-alcohol spirits products
41 are resold to vessels of foreign registry for consumption after that vessel has left
42 port or are resold for consumption on board vessels of United States registry that
43 are destined for a foreign port.
