1 (3) The bureau shall grant a credit for the excise tax on malt liquor, wine, spirits
2 cocktail products and low-alcohol spirits products sold to a licensee registered with
3 the bureau for resale to licensed airlines or to unlicensed airlines for their
4 international flights.'
5 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
6 number to read consecutively.
7 SUMMARY
88 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, replaces the bill and
99 changes the title. The amendment defines "spirits cocktail product" to mean a product
1100 packaged as a single-serving ready-to-drink beverage containing spirits that contains more
1111 than 8% alcohol by volume but no more than 15% alcohol by volume. Under the
1122 amendment, a licensed distillery or small distillery is authorized to distill, rectify or blend
1133 spirits cocktail products. Except for spirits cocktail products sold at the manufacturing
1144 facility or at an off-premises location licensed to the distillery, delivery of spirits cocktail
1155 products to licensed retailers must be made by a wholesale licensee in the same manner as
1166 wine. The excise tax on spirits cocktail products under the amendment is $1.24 per gallon
1177 and is paid by the manufacturer or the wholesale licensee.
1188 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
